import React from 'react'
import { Header, Menu, Icon } from 'semantic-ui-react'

const AdminSidebar = props => {
  return (
    <React.Fragment>
      <Header as='h3'>Admin</Header>
      <Menu.Item as='a' onClick={() => props.handleDisplayChange('messages')}>
        <Icon name='envelope outline' />
        Messages
      </Menu.Item>
      <Menu.Item as='a' onClick={() => props.handleDisplayChange('employees')}>
        <Icon name='user' />
        Employees
      </Menu.Item>
      <Menu.Item as='a' onClick={() => props.handleDisplayChange('jobs')}>
        <Icon name='bolt' />
        Jobs
      </Menu.Item>
      <Menu.Item as='a'>
        <Icon name='question circle' onClick={() => props.handleDisplayChange('requests')} />
        Requests
      </Menu.Item>
    </React.Fragment>
  )
}

export default AdminSidebar
